Written evidence submitted by Principal Forensic Services Ltd (PFS) (FSS004)[bold]&#xa0;[bold]Declaration of Interests[bold]Does the Government have an effective strategy for forensic science in the UK and is it sufficient to support forensic science R&amp;D and criminal justice?[bold]Did the FSS transition and closure run smoothly and within budget?[bold]What impacts have the FSS’s closure had on ([bold]i[bold]) the criminal justice system and (ii) forensic science R&amp;D and training? In particular, have the appropriate quality standards and accreditation been rigorously maintained? [bold](i)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Impact on [bold]CJS[bold](ii)[bold]&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; 
[normal]Impact on [bold]Forensic Science R&amp;D and Training[bold]What should be role of the Forensic Science Regulator?[bold]What is the size of the forensics market and how stable is it?[bold]How are forensic science services procured by police forces and could procurement processes be improved?[bold]Has the closure of the FSS resulted in a loss of intellectual wealth through its scientists leaving the forensic science profession, or the UK? (please provide evidence/examples)[bold]Are current arrangements for the FSS’s archives satisfactory? How could arrangements for the retention of case files and forensic materials in the UK be improved?[bold]January 2013
